<body>

    <article class="blog-container">
        <header class="blog-header">
            <h1>Xoloitzcuintle Sizes Explained: Toy, Miniature, and Standard</h1>
            <div class="blog-meta">
                <span>By <strong>Xolos Ramirez</strong></span> | <span>Published in <em>Breed Guides</em></span>
            </div>
        </header>

        <section class="blog-content">
            <p>Welcome to the <strong>Xolos Ramirez</strong> blog! If you are considering adding a Xoloitzcuintle (Mexican Hairless Dog) to your family, you are stepping into a world of ancient heritage and unparalleled loyalty. One of the most important decisions you'll make is choosing the right size for your lifestyle, as the Xolo breed officially comes in three distinct sizes: <strong>Toy, Miniature, and Standard</strong>.</p>
            
            <p>Despite their size differences, all three varieties share the same primitive elegance, intelligence, and affectionate temperament. Let’s break down the differences so you can find your perfect companion.</p>

            <div class="img-container">
                
            </div>

            <h2>1. The Toy Xoloitzcuintle (El Tamaño Toy)</h2>
            <div class="size-card">
                <div class="size-info">
                    <div class="size-stats">
                        <span class="stat-item">📏 Height: 10 - 14 inches (25 - 35 cm)</span>
                        <span class="stat-item">⚖️ Weight: 10 - 15 lbs (4 - 7 kg)</span>
                    </div>
                    <p>The Toy Xolo is the smallest of the three. Perfect for apartment living and urban environments, these tiny companions are highly alert, affectionate, and fiercely loyal to their owners. Because of their small size, they are easy to travel with. However, don't let their diminutive stature fool you; they possess the same fearless, watchdog instincts as their larger counterparts.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h2>2. The Miniature Xoloitzcuintle (El Tamaño Miniatura)</h2>
            <div class="size-card">
                <div class="size-info">
                    <div class="size-stats">
                        <span class="stat-item">📏 Height: 14 - 18 inches (36 - 45 cm)</span>
                        <span class="stat-item">⚖️ Weight: 15 - 30 lbs (7 - 14 kg)</span>
                    </div>
                    <p>The Miniature Xolo is the "goldilocks" size for many families—not too small, not too big. They are sturdy, athletic, and highly adaptable. Whether you want a dog to join you on moderate hikes or one to snuggle with on the couch, the Miniature size fits the bill perfectly. They do well in both houses with yards and spacious apartments, provided they get enough daily exercise.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h2>3. The Standard Xoloitzcuintle (El Tamaño Estándar)</h2>
            <div class="size-card">
                <div class="size-info">
                    <div class="size-stats">
                        <span class="stat-item">📏 Height: 18 - 23 inches (46 - 60 cm)</span>
                        <span class="stat-item">⚖️ Weight: 30 - 55 lbs (14 - 25 kg)</span>
                    </div>
                    <p>The Standard Xolo is the original, ancient size of the breed. Majestic, robust, and incredibly athletic, this size requires a bit more space and exercise. They make excellent guardians and are known for their calm, noble demeanor at home once their energy is spent. A Standard Xolo commands attention and respect, embodying the ancient spirit of the Aztec guides to the underworld.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="conclusion">
                <p><strong>Which size is right for you?</strong> No matter which size you choose, bringing a Xoloitzcuintle into your life means welcoming a piece of living history. At <em>Xolos Ramirez</em>, we are dedicated to preserving the health, temperament, and legacy of this magical breed across all its beautiful sizes.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
